docs.abstract: For many residents, he represents the Lebanese dream, of leaving the country and becoming a success.
docs.snippet: For many residents, he represents the Lebanese dream, of leaving the country and becoming a success.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIRUT, Lebanon — For weeks last winter, Carlos Ghosn’s face seemed inescapable in the Lebanese capital, appearing without warning on digital billboards normally devoted to ads for cellphone plans and fancy cars. “We are all Carlos Ghosn,” the text announced, declaring support for the man charged in Japan as a corporate titan gone bad.

headline.main: Carlos Ghosn, Fugitive but a Favorite Son, Returns to Beirut
headline.print_headline: Wanted by Japan, and in Beirut

byline.original: By Vivian Yee and Hwaida Saad

docs.abstract: Threats of ‘retribution,’ more accusations of ‘fake news’ and the end of the White House briefing made 2019 the darkest yet for journalists in the Trump era.
docs.snippet: Threats of ‘retribution,’ more accusations of ‘fake news’ and the end of the White House briefing made 2019 the darkest yet for journalists in the Trump era.
docs.lead_paragraph: On Twitter, President Trump deployed the phrase “fake news” 273 times this year — 50 percent more often than he did in 2018. He demanded “retribution” over a “Saturday Night Live” sketch, declared that Washington Post reporters “shouldn’t even be allowed on the grounds of the White House,” and accused The New York Times of “Treason.”

headline.main: After Another Year of Trump Attacks, ‘Ominous Signs’ for the American Press
headline.print_headline: Trump Attacked News Media Even More in 2019

docs.abstract: A Brooklyn wine bar and restaurant is one of a handful of establishments in different cities that are trying to eliminate waste from their premises.
docs.snippet: A Brooklyn wine bar and restaurant is one of a handful of establishments in different cities that are trying to eliminate waste from their premises.
docs.lead_paragraph: Garbage is inevitable in the restaurant and bar business. Kitchen employees toss onion skins and meat fat into the wastebasket almost instinctively. Once-used plastic wrap and slips guarding the linens find their way into black bags for trash-day pickup. Plastic bags are ordered by the bundle and then often discarded after customers use them to take leftovers home.

docs.abstract: The prominent former auto executive eluded the authorities and the news media to flee while awaiting trial, setting off a flurry of speculation.
docs.snippet: The prominent former auto executive eluded the authorities and the news media to flee while awaiting trial, setting off a flurry of speculation.
docs.lead_paragraph: TOKYO — By the time most of Japan had woken up on Tuesday, he was gone. One of the country’s most famous criminal suspects had slipped past the cameras trained on his house, past the police and border guards and the Japanese citizens who for the past year have followed his every move.

headline.main: Carlos Ghosn’s Escape: A Lawyer in Beirut, a French Passport and a Lot of Mystery
headline.print_headline: 3 Passports and a Plan Hatched in Lebanon: Ghosn’s Escape Act

docs.abstract: He Jiankui’s work was also carried out on a third infant, according to China’s state media, in a new disclosure that is likely to add to the global uproar over such experiments.
docs.snippet: He Jiankui’s work was also carried out on a third infant, according to China’s state media, in a new disclosure that is likely to add to the global uproar over such experiments.
docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — A court in China on Monday sentenced He Jiankui, the researcher who shocked the global scientific community when he claimed that he had created the world’s first genetically edited babies, to three years in prison for carrying out “illegal medical practices.”

headline.main: Chinese Scientist Who Genetically Edited Babies Gets 3 Years in Prison
headline.print_headline: Man Who Claimed To Edit Baby Genes Gets Term in Prison

docs.lead_paragraph: Tesla said on Friday that it had produced over 100,000 vehicles and delivered even more in the fourth quarter of 2019, meeting a goal it had laid out to investors and ending the year on stronger footing than at the start.

docs.abstract: The 118 feature-length movies selected for the indie festival include Julianne Moore as Gloria Steinem and a documentary on Parkland survivors.
docs.snippet: The 118 feature-length movies selected for the indie festival include Julianne Moore as Gloria Steinem and a documentary on Parkland survivors.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Oscar winners Julianne Moore and Alicia Vikander are two of the four actresses who play the feminist activist Gloria Steinem at different ages in “The Glorias,” an unconventional biopic from the director Julia Taymor. The film will be among the 118 feature-length works at the 2020 Sundance Film Festival, the programmers announced Wednesday.

headline.main: Sundance Gets Real, With a Lineup of Newsy Films for 2020
headline.print_headline: This Time, the Sundance Festival Lineup Is ‘of the Time’
